{{Primary sources|date=June 2008}} {{Infobox Magazine| title = The Culture Lounge | frequency = Every Other Month | category = Art magazine| founded = 2006 | country = [[United States]] | based = [[Columbus Nebraska]] | website = | }}
'''''The Culture Lounge''''' is a [[visual art]], [[philosophy]], [[literary]], and [[culture]] [[magazine]] that emphasizes diversity and expression through the creative forms.
Published in [[Columbus Nebraska]] since May 2006, the main focus is raising the awareness of the individual and embracing cultural differences throughout the magazine. They have interviewed musicians such as [[Two Gallants (band)|Two Gallants]] and visual artists [[C.Hues]] who did tour posters for [[The Grateful Dead]].
Utilizing the internet has allowed ''Culture Lounge'' to find contributors outside of the [[United States]] and each issue boasts the use and recognition of contributors from around the world.
